tagblock.comment: You can't just poke the following 2 values. In memory they become a pointer, pointing directly to the memory address of the destination shape. If you want to poke it, you'll want to View Value As on the Shape Type enum for its address and use another poking tool to paste the memory address of the new shape. Use the address of the "Size" value.
